{
  "texts": [
    "The most common are age and gender, used at the beginning of each patient sequence (Boursalie et al. 2021; Rao et al. 2022b) or directly in the last layer of the architecture (Fouladvand et al. 2021).",
    "However, some works use the attribute age as a resource to improve the sequential semantic notion (Li et al. 2020; Rao et al. 2022a).",
    "Thus, they support the positional encoding task.",
    "Our review shows that diverse concepts and union of concepts are used as positional encode (InpRQ4).",
    "For example, the sinusoidal function (Florez et al. 2021; Li et al. 2021; Darabi et al. 2020), which is used in the original transformer paper (Devlin et al. 2018), simple sequential values (Rasmy et al. 2021; Li et al. 2023a, b; Rao et al. 2022b), and calendar dates (Zeng et al. 2022; Dong et al. 2021)."
  ]
}